title: Учение Христа, изложенное для детей
creator: Leo Tolstoy
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Учение Христа, изложенное для детей, by Leo Tolstoy. Read by Vladimir Anyanov. In 1908 Leo Tolstoy organized a school for peasant children, age 10-13, in his house. During lessons he expounded them the most clear and important passages from Gospels. From those conversations Tolstoy composed that book. (Summary by Vladimir Anyanov) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; christianity; religion; children; Jesus Christ
